The paper presents a new framework for complex support vector regression (SVR) and Support Vector Machines (SVM) for quaternary classification. The method employs complex-valued data and uses Wirtinger’s calculus on complex reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces to compute the Lagrangian and derive the dual optimization problem. This work is related to machine learning (ML) and pattern recognition, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the development of new ML algorithms and frameworks. The paper also deals with neural networks and optimization, which are covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of SVMs and kernels makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves image processing and computer vision, which are covered by cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper deals with signal processing and statistical learning, which are covered by cs.SI (Signal Processing).
